Naming and shaming can very easily, and often does create toxic behaviour and 'witch hunts' which is not good for the community. If you report someone via the in-game system and have additional information you wish to add that you may not have popped into your in-game report, you can then open a support ticket and pass the information on through there to aid the investigation into the player. I think that's the point Sephyre was getting to with the support ticket.

I dislike toxic behaviour as much as the next person, and by reporting offending players and not contributing to toxic behaviour is how we can help overcome it
